
[1]clothes

   CLOTHES, n. plu. Of cloth; pronounced cloze.

   1. Garments for the human body; dress; vestments; vesture; a general
   term for whatever covering is worn, or made to be worn, for decency or
   comfort.

   If I may touch but his clothes, I shall be whole. Mark 5.

   2. The covering of a bed; bed-clothes.
